  <span id="freeText2927416384663819414" style="display:none">Such a powerful and incredibly moving novel, quite unforgettable. I recommend you read the book then watch the film, both are intense yet wonderful!<br /><br />This story is of two southern families that live through unbearable circumstance during the Jim Crow era. So many struggles and hardships abound that had my heart aching. And near the ending that brutal scene with Ronsel will haunt me for a while. This book is gut wrenching and has highly sensitive issues that will bring tears to your eyes. Loved this and highly recommend. I rated all the stars. </span>
